						<summary>

						<p>Slab (No. 5) lying near the P.W.D. office.</p>						

						<p>1683 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record in characters of about the 17th century seems to register a gift to god Mūlasthāna Mallikārjuna probably by the <hi rend="italic">gavuḍa, sēnabōva</hi> and others.</p>						

						<p>It is dated the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Rudhirōdgār in, Āśvija śu. [3, Monday],</hi> probably corresponding to 1683 A.D., September 10, Monday f.d.t. ·60.</p>						

						</summary>
